Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.44,0:00:09.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kagami Yoshimizu Theater"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.27,0:00:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.88,0:00:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.88,0:00:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grr!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.52,0:00:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit screwing around and start!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.36,0:00:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The ambiguous 3cm?\NDoes that mean it's plushy? Wait!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wrapping is a uniform, argh,\Nit's not an act, pooh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.57,0:00:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotta do your best, gotta just do it{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.29,0:00:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's time to catch 'n' release, eek{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.91,0:00:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Between sweat (whoop)\NSweat (whoop){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.73,0:00:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Darlin', darlin', freeze! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.59,0:00:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kinda lethargic,\Nsomething's kinda comin' out{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I love you... Oh wait,\None of those was different{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worrywarts, high metal bars {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.20,0:00:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tasty thoughts... And that's enough!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.93,0:00:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heated body of that\Nflying you-know-who{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.72,0:00:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's what you call a normal girlie{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.43,0:00:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Am I the only one surprised? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.60,0:00:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seconds on pork-bone broth ramen\Nwith wire-hard noodles{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.77,0:00:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Da da da da da {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.98,0:00:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pom-poms cheer squad{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.77,0:00:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's get cherry pie {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happy fun welcoming party {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.87,0:00:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look up! Sensation{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.46,0:00:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah! Feeling of existence,\Ndot dot small planet{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.58,0:00:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Collided and it melted away,\Nin total awe{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.20,0:01:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go all out to sing, shi-ranger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.91,0:01:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Take it away! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.12,0:01:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I should be the one who'll be\Nlaughing in the end{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.49,0:01:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because I have the sailor suit\N← This is my conclusion{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.51,0:01:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's only Monday! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.82,0:01:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Already in a bad mood? What to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.37,0:01:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I really prefer the summer outfits\N← kya! Wah! Good! (cute!) < 3{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.14,0:01:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Until we approach 3 pixels,\Nno hesitations please ★{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.39,0:01:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do your best, be energetic {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.02,0:01:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My darlin', darlin' please! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.12,0:01:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They bought me a new cell phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.70,0:01:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't put it in the laundry this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.28,0:01:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'll keep it\Nsomewhere noticeable!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.30,0:01:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tsukasa, help me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.99,0:01:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.79,0:01:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Desires"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.16,0:02:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-a-l-s-a-m-i-c V-i-n-e...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.47,0:02:08.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Irritated"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.73,0:02:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There. ...g-a-r.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.62,0:02:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll type them all in for you,\Nso hand it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.27,0:02:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're irritating me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.45,0:02:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay. It's all right,\NI'll do it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.08,0:02:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to visit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.62,0:02:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Sis. Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.41,0:02:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you playing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.04,0:02:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gal-game that came out recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.86,0:02:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll pick some\Nrandom manga to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.66,0:02:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.52,0:02:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an age-restricted title...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.07,0:02:40.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does she not realize it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.25,0:02:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or is she letting it slide\Nwithout a thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.03,0:02:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is it, oh, police officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.76,0:02:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, we're having Traffic Safety Week,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.74,0:02:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and so we're stepping up\Non the ticketing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.55,0:02:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have really nit-picky checks to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.16,0:02:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we have to take the time\Nto explain all the traffic rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.45,0:02:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really a big burden!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.60,0:02:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, the offender gets\Nmad at me for doing it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.04,0:03:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, seeing you and\Nhow you usually act...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.12,0:03:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rules and safety hold\Nno persuasive powers at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.17,0:03:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really a surprise to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.78,0:03:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shikina Shima Clinic"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.81,0:03:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that this year's cold\Nlasts for quite a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.21,0:03:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I must get better quickly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.21,0:03:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the reception number,\Nit looks like it will take a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.93,0:03:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just read a book and wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.67,0:03:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Ando? Mr. Shigeo Ando?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.62,0:03:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Takara? Miss Miyuki Takara?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.78,0:03:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Miss Miyuki Takara not here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then next, Miss Mariko Nishiyama?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.40,0:03:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.88,0:03:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was my name called?\NWhat time is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.60,0:04:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must pay attention to\Nmy surroundings a bit more...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.63,0:04:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are approaching Kamata,\Nour final stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.39,0:04:11.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.22,0:04:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, I taught Tsukasa\Nhow to send text messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.60,0:04:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She told me she didn't know how,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.08,0:04:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after fiddling around with it so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.87,0:04:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.44,0:04:26.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yay!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.72,0:04:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she must have been terribly happy about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.20,0:04:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because she texts me every day
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.56,0:04:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with anything and everything\Nthat's going on around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fielding all those messages\Nmust be a chore, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.20,0:04:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there's no need to be\Nall worried about it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.71,0:04:34.04,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"From: Tsukasa"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.33,0:04:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the type that gets all\Nworked up in the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.54,0:04:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but always loses wind after a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.68,0:04:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, there's people out there\Nwith such childish tendencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.33,0:04:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I've got another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that they get bored with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.99,0:04:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they just can't keep up\Nwith themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.55,0:04:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, are there that many\Nthings to text about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.69,0:04:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when we're\Ntogether all the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.38,0:04:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and I think she's caught on\Nto the emoticon thing too. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.37,0:04:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to buy the soy-milk cream\Nbuns again on our way home today?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is all this after the sentence?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.25,0:05:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that she's really\Nhaving fun gets across, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.62,0:05:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, it's hieroglyphics.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.14,0:05:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she's gotten used to it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That's true, but I like the guy\Nwith the afro better."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.59,0:05:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Really? But he's not really\Nplaying that instrument, is he?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.30,0:05:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yeah, maybe so."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.26,0:05:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I see."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.02,0:05:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yeah."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.06,0:05:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.92,0:05:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.08,0:05:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand how you feel,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.45,0:05:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but would it kill you to send them\Nto a non-relative sometime?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.57,0:05:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys have a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.52,0:05:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.66,0:05:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really understand how to\Nsend messages on my cell phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.60,0:05:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.83,0:05:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's easy, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.38,0:05:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess it can't be helped.\NI'll show you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at you, boasting like that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.84,0:06:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you just learned how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.86,0:06:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.30,0:06:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just can't put that\Nstench into words.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.18,0:06:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it really stinks too bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.18,0:06:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.43,0:06:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you've got quite a lot\Nof people entered in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.82,0:06:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Don't peek without asking!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.65,0:06:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have messages you don't\Nwant others to see or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. I just felt I should say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.61,0:06:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A guy! It must be a guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.45,0:06:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, it's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.28,0:06:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not picking up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.78,0:06:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll call her house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.09,0:06:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Kagami.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.20,0:06:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Konata? How about\Nanswering your cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.46,0:06:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I didn't realize you called\N'cause the ringer is turned off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.79,0:06:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't tell you've\Ngot a call, it's pointless!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.21,0:06:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For that matter, where is that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.70,0:07:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your cell phone really is pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.23,0:07:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, about this\Ncoming weekend...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.24,0:07:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wait, I'm being paged. Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.44,0:07:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.67,0:07:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on for a minute more.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.16,0:07:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're talking too long!\NI can't wait anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.90,0:07:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.41,0:07:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He scolded me for talking\Ntoo long on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.76,0:07:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.16,0:07:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought your house was rather\Nlaid-back with that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.02,0:07:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But is it actually pretty strict?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.54,0:07:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we're in the middle\Nof a fighter-game match.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.47,0:07:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mention stuff like that\Nearlier in the conversation!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.51,0:07:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Past and present, discount cards\Nhave invisible magical powers...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.20,0:07:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before you know it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.27,0:07:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you end up buying things that\Nyou weren't planning on buying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.37,0:07:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't plan\Nanything, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.47,0:07:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I kind of understand\Nhow you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.90,0:07:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.17,0:07:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing that Ani___e and Ga___'s
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.67,0:07:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the two anime shops in this town,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.08,0:08:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she buys the same\Nitem at both stores...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.25,0:08:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Legendary Girl A!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.95,0:08:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Legendary Girl A Shift!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.89,0:08:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.68,0:08:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have {\i1}Haruhi {\i0}vol. 5\Non DVD in stock now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.40,0:08:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both the limited and standard edition,\Nhere to perfection!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.86,0:08:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Other than that, all sorts of goods\Nare coming in one after another!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inform her of what we have in stock,\Nas much as you possibly can.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.05,0:08:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's her, I'm sure she'll buy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.17,0:08:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I was going after the special\Nbookmark gift for {\i1}Aquarian Age{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.15,0:08:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to go to Gamers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.22,0:08:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No good!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.29,0:08:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.87,0:09:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll have\Na sleepover this weekend,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.80,0:09:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and play all through the night!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.20,0:09:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.04,0:09:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we get together to play,\Nit's always at my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.31,0:09:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't we go to your place, Konata?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to visit every so often.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.64,0:09:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that you guys\Ncan't come over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.04,0:09:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that Dad's usually home,\Nbecause of his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.68,0:09:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.91,0:09:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, and I don't want to be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.58,0:09:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,held responsible for anything\Nthat might happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.00,0:09:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.92,0:09:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"O-Agariyasu"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.96,0:09:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kind of looking forward to\Nwhat Konata's house is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.84,0:09:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S'up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.84,0:09:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.59,0:09:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse us... We'll be under\Nyour care for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.68,0:09:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome. I hear about\Nyou guys a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear your house is a shrine,\Nso does that makes you shrine maidens?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.28,0:09:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What kind of an explanation\Nhave you been giving?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.99,0:09:48.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--So do you usually wear those frilly hakama pants?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.07,0:09:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Or rather, is that the very first thing you have to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.30,0:09:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.87,0:09:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0}'s room!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.10,0:09:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I expected,\Nthis is an amazing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.45,0:10:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.21,0:10:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, a door...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.76,0:10:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure this is the room\Nto remain unopened,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.34,0:10:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,full of stuff that you can't\Nrisk having seen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, stuff like that\NI usually share with Dad,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.28,0:10:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so they're all kept in Dad's study.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.76,0:10:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, you share them...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,\Nyour dad's an author, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.24,0:10:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.87,0:10:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, do you get hooked\Non the light novels
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.16,0:10:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or the gal-games that\Nyour dad scripts?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.37,0:10:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he doesn't write that kind\Nof stuff at all in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.68,0:10:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.79,0:10:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.62,0:10:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... That's rather unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.72,0:10:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he likes that genre,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.08,0:10:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so doesn't he feel like\Nwriting something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.74,0:10:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call him a strict lurker.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.88,0:10:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said something like
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.32,0:10:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was playing a gal-game, or rather,\Na nurturing game in real life,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.24,0:10:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he didn't feel the need\Nto do more of it as work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.36,0:10:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.44,0:10:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I've been overwhelmed\Nsince I got here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.80,0:10:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing less from\Nthe Izumi household!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.07,0:11:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other day,\NDad was being all clingy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.74,0:11:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.41,0:11:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I told him "Dad, you're so\Nannoying!" as an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.93,0:11:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, that's being a bit rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.48,0:11:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I did, Dad scolded me like,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.56,0:11:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"At least, say 'Dad, I hate you so\Nmuch!' or something like that."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.67,0:11:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I'm not so sure about\Nthat correction either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.23,0:11:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling that you and Dad\Nare thinking different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.94,0:11:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You already lost me anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.52,0:11:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to take a break soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.04,0:11:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.31,0:11:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, lately there's a lot\Nof 2ch-speak on TV and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.84,0:11:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe so. Though I don't\Nknow too much about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.67,0:11:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Konata,\Nyou're pretty hardcore,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.19,0:11:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you don't use those\Nkinds of words too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.65,0:11:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I normally don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.34,0:11:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm chatting online\Nand stuff, I talk like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.14,0:11:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! Is that really Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.73,0:11:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I've lost if people can read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.15,0:12:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want me to help with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.07,0:12:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, then can you dish up the salad?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.36,0:12:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.87,0:12:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the food!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.74,0:12:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.19,0:12:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. This is pretty good!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.24,0:12:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This much is no big deal if you\Nalways do your household chores.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.58,0:12:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami, why don't you help out\Nmore? You might get a little better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.92,0:12:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need your advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.22,0:12:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Konata, it's perfect...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.59,0:12:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A scene that I have only dreamt of\Nis in front of my eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.65,0:12:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Three high-school girls surrounding\Na guy at the dinner table
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.74,0:12:39.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--I can forget about everything else...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.53,0:12:44.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Sakura... Tohsaka... Tohsaka is your older sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.92,0:12:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Is an unnaturally frequent situation in gal-games, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.53,0:12:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Oh... So that's it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.65,0:12:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sure gets cold at this time of day!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.41,0:12:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should have worn\Nsomething on top of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.12,0:12:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, a shooting star!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.02,0:13:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I couldn't say\Nmy wish three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.66,0:13:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They come so suddenly,\Nit's rather hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.96,0:13:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But someday, I'm going to succeed,\Nand it'll grant me a wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.44,0:13:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa, you're always a dreamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.56,0:13:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But no matter how you think\Nabout it, it's just impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.56,0:13:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They only made that legend because\Nyou know there's no way to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.40,0:13:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And why is this end\Nso lacking in dreams?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys want some, Kagami?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.68,0:13:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.62,0:13:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You switched hairdos.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.62,0:13:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, just playing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.28,0:13:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we got to take baths before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.41,0:13:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it that the image gained\Nfrom certain equipment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.58,0:13:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so different depending\Non who's wearing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.38,0:13:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's an album.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.01,0:13:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I take a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.20,0:13:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.47,0:13:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you're so cute, Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.31,0:13:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your looks really haven't\Nchanged at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.54,0:13:54.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, in your family,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.30,0:13:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,father and child get along so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.89,0:13:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.77,0:14:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a chi-- No, so young!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.64,0:14:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She looks like me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.66,0:14:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope it wasn't a crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.57,0:14:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I look at Dad, I always think...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.25,0:14:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...what part of Dad\Ndid Mom find attractive?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.24,0:14:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look so much like your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.06,0:14:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, for instance,\Nwhat kind of guy is your type?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.59,0:14:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.98,0:14:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you put it that way,\NI really don't have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.64,0:14:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Just say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.92,0:14:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.76,0:14:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, maybe Mom was\Nhappy with just about anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.84,0:14:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said that Dad was\Na childhood friend of hers too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.70,0:14:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, of all things, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.70,0:14:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she picked him because\Nshe felt sorry for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really show no mercy,\Neven to your own parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.85,0:14:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, looking at Mom,\NI had a thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.86,0:14:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.83,0:14:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manga and games lately\Nhave lots of characters
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.52,0:14:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like junior high kids that\Nare mature for their age,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.66,0:14:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or adults who act immature.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.55,0:14:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that? Are you angling\Nfor a comeback line?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.45,0:14:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have been nice if\NYuki-{\i1}chan {\i0}could come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.46,0:15:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she had an errand to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.04,0:15:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know! I'll text Yuki-{\i1}chan\N{\i0}so she won't feel lonely!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.20,0:15:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki is probably sensitive\Nabout that kind of stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.52,0:15:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it's better if you don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.88,0:15:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she replied.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.65,0:15:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad that you are\Nhaving a fun time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.59,0:15:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, I am doing my best\Nto finish my homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.72,0:15:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, I will make sure to...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.52,0:15:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot that we had homework!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.13,0:15:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami, do something about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.91,0:15:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't have any in our class,\Nso can I go to sleep now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.79,0:15:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.24,0:15:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That shooting star from earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.74,0:15:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I can make something of it\Nif I make my wish shorter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.52,0:15:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.82,0:15:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.27,0:15:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Researching how to say my wish\Nto a shooting star faster...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.77,0:15:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go escaping from reality,\Nand hurry and finish up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.33,0:15:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.01,0:15:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't understand this part\Nduring class earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.43,0:15:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that part?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.20,0:16:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kona-{\i1}chan {\i0}comes from Konata,\NYuki-{\i1}chan {\i0}comes from Miyuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Tsukasa, what kind of\Na nickname would you give Kagami?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.63,0:16:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaga-{\i1}chan{\i0}? Gami-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.03,0:16:14.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mirror (Kagami / kyou)"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.27,0:16:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it would be Kyou-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.81,0:16:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like, Kyou... the other way to read the kanji for "kagami."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.68,0:16:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you've got good taste there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.28,0:16:17.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Power (tsuyo-i / kyou)"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.64,0:16:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It portrays that really tough-willed personality of hers perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.53,0:16:26.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ominous (kyou)"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.60,0:16:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, you can turn it into this kind of Kyou-{\i1}chan {\i0}too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.66,0:16:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I meant, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.97,0:16:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you'd be better off not telling Sis that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.41,0:16:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then if you were to give yourself\Na nickname, what would it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.23,0:16:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsuka-{\i1}chan{\i0}? Kasa-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.42,0:16:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably Hii-{\i1}chan{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.80,0:16:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to come up with\Na nickname from my first name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.00,0:16:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It's true that you\Nhave an image like
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.27,0:16:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you're always shrieking\Naround like, "Hee! Hee!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.46,0:16:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though that's not\Nwhat I meant either...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.64,0:16:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.59,0:16:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, I'll call you\NHii-{\i1}chan{\i0}, Tsukasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.65,0:16:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.39,0:16:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, "Eh?" Huh? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.77,0:16:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, don't you somehow\Nget a bad feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.75,0:16:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about a nickname that\Nyou came up with?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.70,0:16:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, how about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.16,0:16:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.75,0:16:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything will do, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.21,0:17:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to seek\Nrevenge, Sebastian?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.92,0:17:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Shiraishi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.62,0:17:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kyou-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kyou-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.66,0:17:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me that's\Nyou calling for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.08,0:17:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it, so cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.46,0:17:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, what do you\Nwant me to call you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.65,0:17:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't Kagami good enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.41,0:17:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you have a nickname?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.24,0:17:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0} and Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.81,0:17:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, how about Kagami-{\i1}sama{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.27,0:17:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kagami-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wah! She's seriously using it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.69,0:17:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.75,0:17:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, just calling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.31,0:17:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to make you wait,\NKagami-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.53,0:17:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Is something wrong, Kagami-{\i1}sama{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.53,0:17:40.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Huh? Did she just call her Kagami-{\i1}sama{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.60,0:17:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I'm sorry, it's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.64,0:17:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So please, call me\Nlike you normally do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.31,0:17:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Channel{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.07,0:17:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning Luckies!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.72,0:17:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, time passes by quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.19,0:17:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and {\i1}Lucky Channel {\i0}has surged\Ninto its tenth episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.57,0:17:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Akira Kogami, your navigator!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.47,0:18:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello! I'm Minoru Shiraishi,\Nher assistant!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.60,0:18:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll quickly move on, to\Nthe fourth character introduction!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.12,0:18:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to talk about\NKagami Hiiragi today!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.69,0:18:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The realist keeping the silliness\Nat bay in the main segment!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.73,0:18:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So in other words,\Nshe's just a {\i1}tsundere{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.03,0:18:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's so easy to understand.\NWhat a shallow character.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.99,0:18:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to disagree, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.25,0:18:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it's jumping\Nto conclusions a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.34,0:18:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to say that Miss Kagami is a {\i1}tsundere{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.79,0:18:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.46,0:18:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, do we not have\Na true understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.25,0:18:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the term "{\i1}tsundere{\i0}" to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.19,0:18:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it is a sad fact that in this day\Nand age, in an inverse fashion,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.56,0:18:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as the term {\i1}tsundere {\i0}becomes\Nmore and more mainstream,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.38,0:18:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the meaning gets\Nmore and more muddled.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.53,0:18:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place,\Nthe term {\i1}tsundere {\i0}originated
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.69,0:18:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the year 2002 on the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.20,0:18:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, its meaning was\Nprickly ({\i1}tsun-tsun{\i0}) at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.92,0:18:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but later fawning ({\i1}dere-dere{\i0}).
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.76,0:18:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, in other words,\Nit was a term that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.02,0:18:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pointed to a change of heart\Nas time passed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.31,0:18:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really know\Nthe meaning of hits?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.35,0:18:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, it is understood\Nas a portrayal
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.36,0:18:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the two sides of a character's\Npersonality, in other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.89,0:18:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she acts prickly on the outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.40,0:19:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but her true self really\Nfawns over things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.20,0:19:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will go out of my way to say it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.53,0:19:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that it is all a clear misunderstanding!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.48,0:19:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must bring back the\Ntrue definition of {\i1}tsundere{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.24,0:19:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and ring a warning bell to\Nthe fallen linguistic society!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.92,0:19:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stand up, fellow citizens!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.95,0:19:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice going, Sebastian.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.04,0:19:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.82,0:19:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, if Kagami isn't a {\i1}tsundere{\i0},\Nwhat is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.33,0:19:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.09,0:19:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't understand\Nthe complicated stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.43,0:19:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you're going to go that far,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.35,0:19:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,isn't there some term\Nwith the same meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.25,0:19:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as the current usage of {\i1}tsundere{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.76,0:19:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um, I don't think that\Nthere is a lack of such a word...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.84,0:19:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps "cool-dere"...\NNo, that's not it..."{\i1}Dere-tsun{\i0}"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.49,0:19:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have absolutely no taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.96,0:19:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't {\i1}tsundere {\i0}good enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.74,0:19:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's... That's different!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.85,0:19:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.87,0:19:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have our viewers\Nthink of a new concept
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.68,0:19:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that will be able to replace {\i1}tsundere{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.95,0:19:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.66,0:19:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to leave it to others?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.93,0:19:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, all of you in front of your TVs...\Nyes, I mean you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.48,0:19:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you try coming up with a word\Nto describe a character like Miss Kagami?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.16,0:20:02.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And let's use that to overwrite the\NCommon Facts of Modern Speech!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.33,0:20:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call it "The Complete\NDebate of {\i1}Tsundere{\i0}!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.41,0:20:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For details, please check out\Nthe radio show or our homepage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.17,0:20:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be waiting for your\Npassionate input!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.80,0:20:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wrap it up here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.27,0:20:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.68,0:20:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lots and lots, lots and lots...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.15,0:20:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-nee.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.53,0:20:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-nee!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.08,0:20:24.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fast forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.52,0:20:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I really spoke\Na whole bunch today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.44,0:20:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the best take I've had so far!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.30,0:20:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.28,0:20:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}, is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.34,0:20:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.53,0:20:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Well, I spoke the most\Ntoday of all the episodes,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.42,0:20:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I think I did a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.57,0:20:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to eat with the president\Nof your production company,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.20,0:20:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and one of the producers...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.87,0:20:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Eh, what...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.39,0:20:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know, about what's going\Nto happen to you from now on...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.75,0:20:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uh... Hold on just a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.43,0:20:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.20,0:20:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whether or not someone\Ncan keep going on isn't something
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.60,0:20:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that they'd understand,\Neven if told directly to their face.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.69,0:21:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.27,0:21:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have that part-time job\Nat CoCo-(ichi) for now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.15,0:21:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, that's just\Nduring daylight hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.86,0:21:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that I can make\Na fortune out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.59,0:21:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that Korean BBQ place?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.45,0:21:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do work at a Korean BBQ place too...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.07,0:21:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, no, stuff like that\Nreally doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.72,0:21:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's, you know, too private\Na matter, so please stop it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.09,0:21:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm up next.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.96,0:21:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa, how about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.24,0:21:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, if it's this... Right, Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.66,0:21:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.86,0:21:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you guys sing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.60,0:21:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.96,0:21:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.24,0:21:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.36,0:21:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa, you guys decided on a song?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.85,0:21:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.52,0:21:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Lonely, showing an almost\Nbroken self in the window ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.42,0:21:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This song was popular back when\Nwe were in kindergarten, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.16,0:21:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.43,0:21:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I don't know either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.41,0:21:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember! Our big sisters\Nused to sing it a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.98,0:21:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Songs that your parents\Nor older siblings sing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.91,0:21:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are usually a generation before you,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.88,0:21:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you learn them\Nso naturally through them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.85,0:22:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I always looked for something\Nthat would keep it together ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.50,0:22:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Why was it that I couldn't\Nsee dreams so honestly? ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.39,0:22:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ There is no place for me to sleep\Nanywhere in the city ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.88,0:22:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Love was pouring out\Nfrom all over my body ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.00,0:22:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she gave in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.52,0:22:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help it. It's too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.89,0:22:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Through the throng...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.46,0:22:46.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Next Episode Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.28,0:22:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what's with the\Nnext episode of {\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.96,0:22:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.06,0:22:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you go out with friends\Nand eat a meal out,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.48,0:22:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's all right to the point where\Nyou order something with soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.80,0:22:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when the soup splashes and\Na little bit gets on your clothes,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.47,0:22:57.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,doesn't it get a bit depressing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.05,0:22:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially if it was\Nthe curry roux, it's the pits!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.98,0:23:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And those times are always when\Nyou're wearing your favorite outfit,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.86,0:23:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you're totally blue\Nfor the rest of the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.07,0:23:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when you buy a boxed lunch\Nwith soup at a convenience store,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.37,0:23:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you walk home being really careful\Nto keep the contents level
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.82,0:23:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so they don't spill out and stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.28,0:23:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when you get home\Nand open the bag,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.72,0:23:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the soup spilled out and\Nmade a complete mess of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.98,0:23:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you really lose the will to\Neat the lunch altogether!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.25,0:23:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or like, it's nice of them
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.88,0:23:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to separate the hot stuff from the\Ncold when they bag what you buy,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.60,0:23:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but when they put magazines in the\Nsame bag as all your cold drinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.62,0:23:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the paper sucks up all the\Ncondensation from the drinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.26,0:23:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the magazine gets\Nall warped and stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.13,0:23:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did they separate the bags\Nin the first place?! You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.01,0:23:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode: Various Ways\Nto Spend Christmas Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.06,0:23:43.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Various Ways to Spend Christmas Eve"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.81,0:23:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please look forward to it!
